{"bill":{"bill_id":1701974,"change_hash":"e5798bd70b5bedc00a271111188d424c","session_id":2020,"session":{"session_id":2020,"state_id":13,"year_start":2023,"year_end":2024,"prefile":0,"sine_die":0,"prior":0,"special":0,"session_tag":"Regular Session","session_title":"2023-2024 Regular Session","session_name":"103rd General Assembly"},"url":"https:\/\/legiscan.com\/IL\/bill\/SB1830\/2023","state_link":"https:\/\/www.ilga.gov\/legislation\/BillStatus.asp?DocNum=1830&GAID=17&DocTypeID=SB&SessionID=112&GA=103","completed":0,"status":1,"status_date":"2023-02-09","progress":[{"date":"2023-02-09","event":1},{"date":"2023-02-09","event":9},{"date":"2023-02-22","event":9}],"state":"IL","state_id":13,"bill_number":"SB1830","bill_type":"B","bill_type_id":"1","body":"S","body_id":36,"current_body":"S","current_body_id":36,"title":"CONTROLLED SUBSTANCE-PENALTIES","description":"Amends the Criminal Identification Act. Provides that a petitioner may file a petition to vacate and expunge certain felony possession violations under the Illinois Controlled Substances Act or the Methamphetamine Control and Community Protection Act. Amends the Counties Code. Provides that the States Attorney's office of each county shall report annually to the Sentencing Policy Advisory Council certain information regarding each person whose case was disposed under the Illinois Controlled Substances Act, the Cannabis Control Act, and the Methamphetamine Control and Community Protection Act. Amends the Illinois Controlled Substances Act. Provides that notwithstanding any provision of the statute prohibiting the knowing manufacture, delivery, or intent to manufacture or deliver a controlled substance to the contrary, this provision does not apply to possession with intent to deliver an amount of a controlled or counterfeit substances or controlled substance analogs for which possession is classified as a Class A misdemeanor. Reduces the penalties for the knowing manufacture or delivery, possession with int